# 🇧🇪 ShuddhiCheck AI – Phase II: Belgium Readiness

This folder contains the official readiness brief and expansion plan for ShuddhiCheck AI’s Phase II rollout in Belgium.

📄 [Download Belgium Readiness Brief (PDF)](./ShuddhiCheckAI_PhaseII_Belgium_Readiness.pdf)

---

## 📌 Key Highlights

- Multilingual public health governance (Dutch, French, German)
- GDPR compliance overseen by APD/GBA (Belgian DPA)
- EU AI Act integration through FPS Health and Sciensano
- Cross-regional pilot strategy in Brussels, Flanders, and Wallonia
- English supported in pilot rollouts, academic hospitals, and innovation settings

---

## 🏛️ Governance & Innovation Partners

- FPS Public Health, Food Chain Safety and Environment
- Sciensano – Belgian National Institute for Health
- Belgian Data Protection Authority (APD/GBA)
- eHealth Platform Belgium
- Pilot hospitals: UZ Brussel, Saint-Luc University Hospital

---

## 🌐 Language & Localization

| Language | Region       | Status |
|----------|--------------|--------|
| **Dutch**   | Flanders     | ✅ Required |
| **French**  | Wallonia, Brussels | ✅ Required |
| **German**  | Eastern communities | 🟡 Optional (Phase III) |
| **English** | Brussels, research/AI pilots | ✅ Supported for pilots |

🟢 Dashboard pilots will be deployed bilingually (Dutch + French). English versions available for demos.

---

## 🛠️ Next Steps

- Upload PDF readiness brief
- Reach out to Sciensano and FPS Health
- Begin multilingual pilot dashboard preparation (Dutch + French + English)
